stories.text:
With the year coming to an end, what is on your reading list for the year ahead, that you're excited to get into? Here's a few of my own to start things off -

- Finish reading "Code: The Hidden Language of Computer Hardware and Software". I'm hoping as I look to take an extended break, I'll be able to spend more time creating some fun projects off the back of the book, cementing what is taught.

- "Project Hail Mary" by Andy Weir, I enjoyed martians, and I'm keen to keep extending my fiction library (after largely focusing on non-fiction for the past few years).

- "Exhalation" by Ted Chiang. Last year I read "Stories of your life and others", and really enjoyed the writing style, I would like to continue to explore more work by Ted.

- "Notes on a nervous planet" by Matt Haig. I can relate highly to this authors view on the current world climate, and am enjoying working through his catalogue.
